# Memory hardening after Gateway-OOM incident 2026-04-17 16:11 UTC.
# Root cause: V8 default heap limit was hit before systemd-level MemoryMax, causing
# hard V8 OOM crash (status=6/ABRT, core-dump) while MemoryMax=2560M had headroom.
# Fix: raise V8 heap limit to 4 GB, raise systemd cap accordingly.
[Service]
Environment=NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096
MemoryMax=4500M
